#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:6 a47601aef9ab4fe8bf562cd90c9a9100
msgid "Properties vs. Methods"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:8 87ddc4d8594f42e0ba86d2c93d64fe13
msgid ""
"The event shown above acts just like a `custom.Message "
"<telethon.tl.custom.message.Message>`, which means you can access all the"
" properties it has, like ``.sender``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:12 d43a6bd43ce14a17a3cef38f0c10ebbb
msgid ""
"**However** events are different to other methods in the client, like "
"`client.get_messages "
"<telethon.client.messages.MessageMethods.get_messages>`. Events *may not*"
" send information about the sender or chat, which means it can be `None`,"
" but all the methods defined in the client always have this information "
"so it doesn't need to be re-fetched. For this reason, you have ``get_`` "
"methods, which will make a network call if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:19 33a90a425e3740bfb0488e94b31d09d8
msgid "In short, you should do this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:37 52f5e8cd651a4425b12fb6914a28b405
msgid ""
"Notice, properties (`message.sender "
"<telethon.tl.custom.message.Message.sender>`) don't need an ``await``, "
"but methods (`message.get_sender "
"<telethon.tl.custom.message.Message.get_sender>`) **do** need an "
"``await``, and you should use methods in events for these properties that"
" may need network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:44 e4817cad77b746c3b09bf14827cd9e0e
msgid "Events Without the client"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:46 bf5efed1e7414cf6b79c1beba64d9060
msgid ""
"The code of your application starts getting big, so you decide to "
"separate the handlers into different files. But how can you access the "
"client from these files? You don't need to! Just `events.register "
"<telethon.events.register>` them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:63 f5d65e9f48a04a16b51b65138d8eeed6
msgid ""
"Registering events is a way of saying \"this method is an event "
"handler\". You can use `telethon.events.is_handler` to check if any "
"method is a handler. You can think of them as a different approach to "
"Flask's blueprints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:67 cea9bce46fc046b894447ca04a03da3a
msgid ""
"It's important to note that this does **not** add the handler to any "
"client! You never specified the client on which the handler should be "
"used. You only declared that it is a handler, and its type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:71 b4dc9586cf39467a9de948a0a7d48598
msgid ""
"To actually use the handler, you need to `client.add_event_handler "
"<telethon.client.updates.UpdateMethods.add_event_handler>` to the client "
"(or clients) where they should be added to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:86 d28ace8b3e014c5ea9868c79e80c2cfa
msgid ""
"This also means that you can register an event handler once and then add "
"it to many clients without re-declaring the event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:91 874fd9314f9f4669ba67f58dc5ec25ec
msgid "Events Without Decorators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:93 021c1a6889034e9dabb4a08964298801
msgid ""
"If for any reason you don't want to use `telethon.events.register`, you "
"can explicitly pass the event handler to use to the mentioned "
"`client.add_event_handler "
"<telethon.client.updates.UpdateMethods.add_event_handler>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:110 4bc905b611b94ffda4ffb548eeec244f
msgid ""
"Similarly, you also have `client.remove_event_handler "
"<telethon.client.updates.UpdateMethods.remove_event_handler>` and "
"`client.list_event_handlers "
"<telethon.client.updates.UpdateMethods.list_event_handlers>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:115 785c595764f54b4894de7a1b1f7f0a75
msgid ""
"The ``event`` argument is optional in all three methods and defaults to "
"`events.Raw <telethon.events.raw.Raw>` for adding, and `None` when "
"removing (so all callbacks would be removed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/updates.rst:121 b0a74ce5fd77481392db661b41c72aa7
msgid ""
"The ``event`` type is ignored in `client.add_event_handler "
"<telethon.client.updates.UpdateMethods.add_event_handler>` if you have "
"used `telethon.events.register` on the ``callback`` before, since that's "
"the point of using such method at all."
msgstr ""

